    "user_title": "Build Next.js Cache Components Correctly",
    "value_statement": "Cache Components can be hard to adopt safely during Next.js migrations. This skill gives focused guidance for PPR, cache directives, lifetimes, tags, and invalidation.",
    "seo_keywords": [
      "Claude",
      "Codex",
      "Claude Code",
      "Next.js Cache Components",
      "Next.js 16 caching",
      "Partial Prerendering",
      "use cache directive",
      "cacheLife",
      "cacheTag",
      "updateTag"
    ],
    "actual_capabilities": [
      "Explains how to enable Cache Components in next.config.ts.",
      "Distinguishes static, cached, and dynamic route content patterns.",
      "Shows when to use use cache at file, component, and function level.",
      "Documents cacheLife profiles and custom cache lifetime settings.",
      "Covers cacheTag, updateTag, and revalidateTag invalidation choices.",
      "Summarizes migration paths from older Next.js caching options."
    ],
    "limitations": [
      "Focuses on Next.js 16 and newer Cache Components behavior.",
      "Does not inspect a project automatically or run framework diagnostics.",
      "Provides examples, but does not verify database or API implementation details.",
      "Does not replace current Next.js documentation for version-specific changes."
    ],
    "use_cases": [
